# UI Conventions

## Design System

### Color Palette
- **Primary**: `#0080A3` - Main brand color for buttons, links, accents
- **Primary Dark**: `#006280` - Hover states for primary elements
- **Background**: `bg-gray-50` - Main app background
- **Cards**: `bg-white` with `shadow-sm` or `shadow-lg`

### Loading States
Consistent loading components across the app:

```tsx
<div className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center">
  <div className="text-center">
    <div className="animate-spin rounded-full h-12 w-12 border-b-2 border-[#0080A3] mx-auto mb-4"></div>
    <p className="text-gray-600">Chargement...</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Component Architecture

### Layout Components
- [components/Header.jsx](mdc:components/Header.jsx) - Main navigation header
- [components/Sidebar.tsx](mdc:components/Sidebar.tsx) - Collapsible sidebar for authenticated users
- [components/ConditionalLayout.tsx](mdc:components/ConditionalLayout.tsx) - Manages sidebar visibility

### Responsive Design
- **Mobile-first approach**: All components must work on mobile devices
- Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` Tailwind breakpoints consistently
- Sidebar collapses on mobile with hamburger menu
- Cards stack vertically on small screens

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide proper ARIA labels for interactive elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works correctly
- Maintain proper color contrast ratios
- Include loading states with descriptive text

## File Organization

- `/components/` - Reusable UI components
- `/app/*/components/` - Page-specific components
- Prefer TypeScript (.tsx) for new components
- Use consistent naming: PascalCase for components
